# Documentation Language

All project documentation **must be written in English**. This applies to:

- Code comments (inline and block)
- JSDoc / TSDoc annotations
- README files
- Storybook story descriptions, `argTypes` descriptions, and component docs
- Git commit messages
- Pull request titles and descriptions
- Changelog entries
- Cursor rules and any other developer-facing text

## Translation

If documentation, comments, or any developer-facing text is submitted in a language other than English, **automatically translate it to English** before applying or committing the changes. Do not ask for confirmation — just translate and use the English version.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
/** Componente de botón con variantes de estilo */
export const Button = () => { ... };

// ✅ GOOD
/** Button component with style variants */
export const Button = () => { ... };
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Storybook description in Spanish
parameters: {
  docs: {
    description: {
      component: 'Botón con múltiples variantes y tamaños',
    },
  },
}

// ✅ GOOD - Storybook description in English
parameters: {
  docs: {
    description: {
      component: 'Button with multiple variants and sizes',
    },
  },
}
```
